parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the wheels to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The transfer case leaks fluid
the wheels lock up
the vehicle loses control
the transfer case shuts down
and the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission slips
shifts irregularly
leaks fluid
fails to engage gears
and causes the vehicle to jerk or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the clutch slips.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power train can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle's power train fails
causing the vehicle to lose power
and the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to retract properly can cause excessive slack, leading to increased risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly secured.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract on its own
leaving excessive slack
the seat belt gets stuck in the guider/holder
the seat belt twists and becomes unusable
the seat belt only retracts when fed back through the slot manually.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause vibration, shimmying, or shaking of the steering wheel, leading to loss of control of the vehicle, especially at high speeds, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: Warped brake rotors
excessive wear on brake pads
frequent need to replace brake rotors
vibration or shimmying of the steering wheel
shaking of the brake rotors while driving.
